text: Christina Bohannon (born July 2, 1971 in Florida) is an American law professor and Democratic Party politician. In 2000, she moved to the midwest state of Iowa. Bohannon served in the Iowa House of Representatives for the 85th district between 2021 and 2023. In 2022, she lost the nomination to represent Iowa's 1st congressional district to the Republican incumbent Mariannette Miller-Meeks.
